The paper discusses collaborative systems and incentives, which are topics commonly studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions online social computing systems (cs.SI) and credit sharing in scientific co-authorship settings, which are related to topics in computational social science. The use of local sharing rules and the analysis of efficiency suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the fields of cybernetics (cs.CY) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the analysis of optimization and efficiency in collaborative environments suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
